# Rust Code Quality

- Use `anyhow::Result` for fallible functions; never `.unwrap()` or `.expect()` in non-test code
- Add context to propagated errors with `.with_context(|| "...")`
- No `#[allow(dead_code)]` or `#[allow(unused)]` suppressions without a comment explaining why
- For audio callback paths, use lock-free structures (`ringbuf`) -- never hold a mutex in a real-time audio callback
- No commented-out code committed; use `todo!()` or `unimplemented!()` with a tracking comment
- No `clone()` in hot paths (audio processing loop); prefer references or channel messaging
